<div class="memdoc">

<p>Set a local continuation. </p>
<p>The set operation saves the state of the function at the point where the operation is executed. As far as the set operation is concerned, the state of the function does <b>not</b> include the call-stack or local (automatic) variables, but only the program counter and such CPU registers that needs to be saved. </p>

